From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: 2026-05-22T05:35:00Z
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0043-fman-pcd-kg-graft-mode-nia.patch

PR14z15 (2026-05-22): silicon-truth fix for the M2 acceptance gate
CPU regression.  PR14z13 (patch 0042) grafts an ASK CC tree onto an
existing kernel-owned KG scheme by writing KGSE_CCBS via the AR-
mediated RMW primitive keygen_scheme_set_ccbs().  Live silicon
regdump on 2026-05-22 (bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py against DUT
192.168.1.190) confirmed KGSE_CCBS is correctly programmed on the
grafted schemes -- but the M2 metric did not move (6.901 Gbps PASS /
27.26%% kernel-net CPU FAIL vs. <=5%% threshold).

KGSE_MODE NIA encoding (RM 8.7.4, confirmed against SDK
fsl_fman_kg.h fm_kg_build_nia()):

    bits[31]        EN
    bits[30:24]     CCOBASE        (CC group base offset, 8 bits)
    bits[22:18]     NIA engine     (mask 0x007C0000)
                    FM_CTL = 0x00000000   <- route KG -> CC engine
                    BMI    = 0x00500000   <- route KG -> BMI direct
    bits[17:0]      NIA action     (mask 0x0003FFFF)

The silicon dispatcher consults KGSE_CCBS ONLY when the NIA engine
field equals FM_CTL.  With NIA = BMI the scheme enqueues directly to
the kernel's per-CPU RX FQ and the CC engine is never invoked.
keygen_scheme_setup() always sets kgse_mode = (KG_SCH_MODE_EN |
ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA) at scheme-create time, and PR14z13's RMW touches
ONLY kgse_ccbs -- so a freshly-grafted scheme has the CCBS pointer
set but the NIA engine still routing past the CC engine.

Fix: extend keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() to RMW kgse_mode in the SAME
AR-mediated transaction as kgse_ccbs.  Two cases:

  ccbs != 0 (graft):    NIA engine -> FM_CTL, NIA action cleared
  ccbs == 0 (ungraft):  NIA engine -> BMI, action = ENQ_FRAME

Two fields written inside the same indirect window flush as one
atomic WRITE AR.
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
@@ -94,6 +94,16 @@
 #define NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME		0x00000002
 #define ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA		(NIA_ENG_BMI | NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME)
 
+/* PR14z15: KGSE_MODE NIA-engine / NIA-action field masks used by
+ * keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() to flip the NIA engine between BMI
+ * (default, no CC) and FM_CTL (graft active, CC engine invoked).
+ * Silicon ignores KGSE_CCBS unless NIA engine == FM_CTL.  See RM
+ * 8.7.4 and SDK fsl_fman_kg.h fm_kg_build_nia().
+ */
+#define KG_NIA_ENG_MASK			0x007C0000
+#define KG_NIA_AC_MASK			0x0003FFFF
+#define KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL		0x00000000
+
 /* Hard-coded configuration:
  * These values are used as hard-coded values for KeyGen configuration
  * and they replace user selections for this hard-coded version
@@ -609,6 +619,7 @@ int keygen_scheme_set_ccbs(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 	struct fman_kg_regs __iomem *regs;
 	struct keygen_scheme *scheme;
 	u32 ar_reg;
+	u32 mode;
 	int err;
 
 	if (!keygen)
@@ -631,7 +642,22 @@ int keygen_scheme_set_ccbs(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 		return err;
 	}
 
-	/* Modify only kgse_ccbs in the indirect window. */
+	/* PR14z15: rewrite KGSE_MODE NIA engine + action fields in the
+	 * indirect window before flushing.  Without this, a non-zero
+	 * KGSE_CCBS is silently ignored because the silicon dispatcher
+	 * still routes KG -> BMI (the default NIA programmed at
+	 * keygen_scheme_setup() time).  CCOBASE bits[30:24] and the EN
+	 * bit are preserved -- only the NIA engine field flips.
+	 */
+	mode = ioread32be(&regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
+	mode &= ~(KG_NIA_ENG_MASK | KG_NIA_AC_MASK);
+	if (ccbs != 0)
+		mode |= KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL;	/* graft: KG -> CC engine */
+	else
+		mode |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA;	/* ungraft: KG -> BMI default */
+	iowrite32be(mode, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
+
+	/* PR14z13: update KGSE_CCBS (CC tree MURAM offset / 0 to clear). */
 	iowrite32be(ccbs, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_ccbs);
 
 	/* WRITE phase: flush the modified image back. */
